## Working Rules

1. Keep each card between `2` and `4` story points.
2. Treat `parallel_safe: true` as earned evidence, not as a default.
3. Spawn harness subagents in parallel only for cards with disjoint ownership
   and no dependency conflict.
4. Do not run conflicting cards together just to increase concurrency.
5. Update `kanban.json` after every card move.
6. Use atomic commits per card.
7. Treat `kanban.json` as SSOT and Trello as its live projection.
8. Never move a Trello card silently; every move needs a short Russian comment.
9. Before `Review`, run `codex_wp review ...`.
10. Before `Simplification`, run `$code-simplification`.
11. Before `Auto-commit`, run `$auto-commit`.
12. If a card stays above 4 story points, keep the size exception truthful instead of inventing fake slices.

## Move Commands

```bash
node "{{move_script}}" --package-dir "{{package_dir}}" --package-card-id <CARD_ID> --to-list "In progress"
node "{{move_script}}" --package-dir "{{package_dir}}" --package-card-id <CARD_ID> --to-list "Blocked" --blocked-reason "..."
node "{{move_script}}" --package-dir "{{package_dir}}" --package-card-id <CARD_ID> --to-list "Review" --review-selector="--base main" --review-verdict LGTM --review-summary "Ключевой итог ревью."
node "{{move_script}}" --package-dir "{{package_dir}}" --package-card-id <CARD_ID> --to-list "Simplification" --simplification-outcome "Упростил без смены поведения." --simplification-summary "Что именно стало проще."
node "{{move_script}}" --package-dir "{{package_dir}}" --package-card-id <CARD_ID> --to-list "Auto-commit" --commit-sha abc123 --commit-subject "fix: short subject"
node "{{move_script}}" --package-dir "{{package_dir}}" --package-card-id <CARD_ID> --to-list "Done" --done-summary "Итог по карточке."
```

Generated Russian comment shapes:

- `In progress`: `Взял в работу.`
- `Blocked`: `Есть блокер: ...`
- `Review`: `Ревью: LGTM - ...` or `Ревью: BLOCKED - ...`
- `Simplification`: `Упростил: ...`
- `Auto-commit`: `Коммит: abc123 ...` or `Коммит блокирован: ...`
- `Done`: `Готово: ...`

## Recommended Flow

1. Read `kanban.json`.
2. Pick the highest-priority ready cards.
3. If multiple ready cards are marked parallel-safe, launch them in parallel.
4. If a card has dependencies, wait until blockers are done.
5. Sync the matching Trello card move with `move_trello_card.js` and a short Russian comment.
6. Store lane evidence before or with each move.
7. Move finished cards through review, simplification, auto-commit, and done with an updated `kanban.json`.
